review_blob: Pours light amber,crystal clear, with lingering white head.  Notes of citrus and champagne, the latter even more prominent when you taste it.  Balanced and solid, but not spectacular.
On tap at West 50 in Mississauga, ON.  Pours a clear golden hue, with a thin white head that lingers.  Taste rye, floral.  Not unpleasant, but far from earth shattering.
